{-------------------------------------------------------------------
 Versión 2 que mejora semántica y legibilidad respecto a la anterior versión
 Big Block Trade Activity Indicator

 Description:
 Detects the proportion of volume generated by large trades within
 the current bar using intrabar calculations.

 A trade is classified as a "big block trade" if its size exceeds
 the BigBlockTradeSize input.

 The indicator calculates the percentage of volume contributed by
 these large trades and triggers an alert if it exceeds a threshold.

 IntrabarPersist variables are used to maintain state during
 tick-by-tick updates within the current bar.

-------------------------------------------------------------------}

Inputs:
    BigBlockTradeSize(1000),
    AlertThresholdPct(66);

Vars:
    IntrabarPersist CurrentTradeVolume(0),
    IntrabarPersist PreviousTickCount(0),
    IntrabarPersist BigBlockVolume(0),
    IntrabarPersist BigBlockPercentage(0),
    IntrabarPersist TotalTicks(0);


{--------------------------------------------------
 Execute logic only on the most recent bar
--------------------------------------------------}
If LastBarOnChart Then
Begin

    {--------------------------------------------------
     Ensure tick reference exists
    --------------------------------------------------}
    If PreviousTickCount > 0 Then
    Begin

        {----------------------------------------------
         Estimate volume of the latest trade
         (difference in cumulative tick count)
        ----------------------------------------------}
        CurrentTradeVolume = Ticks - PreviousTickCount;

        {----------------------------------------------
         Identify large trades
        ----------------------------------------------}
        If CurrentTradeVolume >= BigBlockTradeSize Then
            BigBlockVolume = BigBlockVolume + CurrentTradeVolume;


        {----------------------------------------------
         Calculate percentage of big block activity
        ----------------------------------------------}
        TotalTicks = Ticks;

        If TotalTicks > 0 Then
            BigBlockPercentage = (BigBlockVolume / TotalTicks) * 100;


        {----------------------------------------------
         Plot block trade percentage
        ----------------------------------------------}
        Plot1(BigBlockPercentage, "BlockPct");


        {----------------------------------------------
         Trigger alert if institutional activity
         exceeds threshold
        ----------------------------------------------}
        If BigBlockPercentage > AlertThresholdPct Then
            Alert("High block trade activity detected");

    End;


    {--------------------------------------------------
     Store current tick count for next update
    --------------------------------------------------}
    PreviousTickCount = Ticks;


    {--------------------------------------------------
     Reset counters at the start of a new bar
    --------------------------------------------------}
    If BarStatus(1) = 2 Then
    Begin
        CurrentTradeVolume = 0;
        PreviousTickCount = 0;
        BigBlockVolume = 0;
        BigBlockPercentage = 0;
    End;

End;


{--------------------------------------------------
 Reference plots
--------------------------------------------------}
Plot2(AlertThresholdPct, "Threshold");
Plot3(0, "ZeroLine");
